 Poultry farmers in Kaduna State are in shock over the reported avian influenza, Bird Flu, outbreak in three local government council areas of the state. According to the Kaduna State Government, the disease is threatening an estimated population of 107, 807 birds, in farms in three local government areas of the state. Commissioner for Agriculture in the state, Ibrahim Hussaini, at a stakeholdersâ€™ meeting with the Poultry Association of Nigeria in Kaduna State, said that the affected farms were located in Chikun, Igabi and Lere local government council areas. Represented by the Director, Veterinary and Livestock Services, Zakariya Pakachi, the commissioner said that tests were conducted by the National Research Veterinary Institute and were positive to highly pathogenic level. He added that already, three farms had been depopulated and decontaminated while result from  the fourth farm was being awaited. 